Top seller from Sotheby's first  Modern and Contemporary African Art sale in London was El Anatsui's Earth Developing More Roots. Sold for £728,750 plus buyer’s premium, it was estimated for sale at between £650,000 and £850,000. 
The aluminum bottle caps and copper wire piece was created in 2011 and has been exhibited at art fairs and curated shows in Delhi, Hong Kong, London and Dakar. 
Source: Sotheby's
